@startuml c4-jotp-07f-sequence-crash-recovery
title JOTP - Crash Recovery Sequence Diagram

participant "Process\nHandler" as Handler
participant "Supervisor" as Supervisor
participant "RocksDBBackend" as RocksDB
participant "AtomicStateWriter" as Writer
participant "EventSourcingAuditLog" as AuditLog
participant "SequencedState" as State

== Normal Operation ==

Handler ->> Handler: handle(state, msg)
note over Handler
  Pure function:
  state + message -> newState
end note

Handler ->> Writer: writeAtomic(key, newState, seqNum)
activate Writer

Writer ->> Writer: codec.encode(newState)
Writer ->> RocksDB: WriteBatch {state, ack}
activate RocksDB

note over RocksDB
  CRITICAL: sync=true
  WAL ensures atomicity
  Either both or neither
end note

RocksDB -->> Writer: success
deactivate RocksDB

Writer -->> Handler: committed
deactivate Writer

Handler ->> State: newState with lastProcessedSeq = seqNum

== JVM Crash ==

participant "JVM Crash!" as Crash #red

Handler -x Crash: SIGKILL / power loss
note over Crash
  Process dies mid-flight
  Mailbox may have unprocessed messages
end note

== Recovery (<1ms detection) ==

Supervisor ->> Supervisor: detect crash via ExitSignal
note over Supervisor
  Linked process exit
  Triggers restart procedure
end note

Supervisor ->> Writer: readWithAck(key)
activate Writer

Writer ->> RocksDB: load(key) + getAckSequence(key)
activate RocksDB
RocksDB -->> Writer: stateBytes, ackSeq
deactivate RocksDB

Writer ->> Writer: verify state.seq == ackSeq

alt Consistency OK
    Writer -->> Supervisor: Optional.of(recoveredState)
else Mismatch (partial write)
    Writer -->> Supervisor: Optional.empty()
    note over Writer
      State/ACK mismatch detected
      Use ACK as source of truth
      Rebuild from events
    end note
end if

deactivate Writer

Supervisor ->> AuditLog: replayHistory(entityId)
activate AuditLog
AuditLog -->> Supervisor: List<AuditEntry>
deactivate AuditLog

note over Supervisor
  Filter: entries where
  entry.seq > lastAckSeq
end note

loop For each unprocessed message (seq > last_acked)
    Supervisor ->> Handler: handle(recoveredState, msg)
    activate Handler

    Handler ->> Handler: idempotent check
    note over Handler
      if (msg.seq <= state.lastSeq)
        return state; // skip duplicate
    end note

    Handler ->> Writer: writeAtomic(key, newState, msg.seq)
    Handler -->> Supervisor: updatedState

    deactivate Handler
end

Supervisor ->> Supervisor: spawn new process with recoveredState
note over Supervisor
  Process resumes from
  last committed state
  No messages lost
  No duplicates processed
end note

@enduml
